parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating that the airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the passenger front airbag is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop lamp switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate
the brake pedal is depressed but the brake lights fail to illuminate
the stop lamp switch warning light remains illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the immobilizer system can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or even safety risks.
symptoms: the immobilizer indicator warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Memory Seat and Mirror Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the memory seat and mirror module can cause the side view mirrors to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The left and right side view mirrors fail to stay in memory position
the mirrors do not adjust correctly
the mirrors do not retain their set position.
